{"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error CS0822\"\nms.date: 07/20/2015\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"CS0822\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"CS0822\"\nms.assetid: 519091be-2332-4df4-acd9-e3b633966b3d\n---\n# Compiler Error CS0822\nImplicitly typed locals cannot be const  \n  \n Implicitly typed local variables are only necessary for storing anonymous types. In all other cases they are just a convenience. If the value of the variable never changes, just give it an explicit type. Attempting to use the `readonly` modifier with an implicitly typed local will generate CS0106.  \n  \n## To correct this error  \n  \n1.  If you require the variable to be constant or `readonly`, give it an explicit type.  \n  \n## Example  \n The following code generates CS0822:  \n  \n```csharp  \n// cs0822.cs  \nclass A  \n{  \n  \n    public static int Main()  \n    {  \n        const var x = 0; // CS0822.cs  \n        return -1;  \n    }  \n}  \n```  \n  \n## See also\n\n- [Implicitly Typed Local Variables](../../csharp/programming-guide/classes-and-structs/implicitly-typed-local-variables.md)\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,165],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"Compiler Error CS0822\"\nms.date: 07/20/2015\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"CS0822\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"CS0822\"\nms.assetid: 519091be-2332-4df4-acd9-e3b633966b3d","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0822","nodes":[{"pos":[0,21],"content":"Compiler Error CS0822","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0822","pos":[0,21]}]}],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[172,193],"content":"Compiler Error CS0822","linkify":"Compiler Error CS0822","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0822","pos":[0,21]}]},{"content":"Implicitly typed locals cannot be const","pos":[194,233]},{"content":"Implicitly typed local variables are only necessary for storing anonymous types.","pos":[240,320]},{"content":"In all other cases they are just a convenience.","pos":[321,368]},{"content":"If the value of the variable never changes, just